President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Xochitl Torres Small as the Deputy Secretary of Agriculture at the U.S Department of Agriculture. Torres Small was previously confirmed by the United States Senate to serve as the Under Secretary for Rural Development. Before that, she served as a United States Representative for New Mexico's second congressional district and was the first woman and person of color to represent that district. Torres Small has a background in working as a Field Representative for Senator Tom Udall, clerking for a United States District Court Judge, and practicing water and natural resources law as an attorney.